sed masks, specially\nconsidering the SEQ and the NEQ individual analysis. Most importantly, the use\nof UT78 washes out the anomaly in the NEQ. Furthermore, we found excess of\nkurtosis, compared with simulations, in the NEQ for the regions not masked by\nUT78 but masked by the other masks, indicating that the previous result could\nbe due to non-removed residual foregrounds by UT78.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 5 Oct 2015 01:07:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-02"}
