 in the numerator\nabove the product term in the Euler Zeta function to make both sides of that\nequation equal with the expectation that that value could be used to predict\nthe number of prime numbers that exist as outputs of the polynomial function\nfor some limit less than or equal to x of the input domain.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 5 Oct 2015 04:34:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 16 Oct 2015 04:11:09 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 14 Dec 2015 18:09:45 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 1 Feb 2016 19:09:22 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Sat, 20 Feb 2016 17:07:51 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Thu, 20 Apr 2023 00:17:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-21"}
